article.headline: Evansville 53, Princeton 32
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. (AP) -- Shy Ely had 12 points and eight rebounds and Jason Holsinger scored 11 to lead Evansville to a 53-32 win over Princeton on Wednesday night. Kavon Lacey had four assists for the Purple Aces (2-4), who outrebounded the Tigers 31-24 and scored 16 points off turnovers. Evansville trailed only once, at 4-3 in the first quarter. The Purple Aces then took a 5-4 lead on a jumper by Holsinger and never looked back. The Purple Aces led 29-12 at the break. Noah Savage, with 12, was the only player in double figures for Princeton (2-6). Evansville shot 22-of-43 overall (51.2 percent) while the Tigers managed just 13-of-39 (33.3 percent). Evansville outscored Princeton 30-18 in the paint.
